Written by Viet Trung Tran

Introduction
============

Read README.en first to understand Gfarm file system

Install
=======
Like installing a Gfarm file system except that:

	+ Install BlobSeer first

	+ WARNING!!! Should have --with-BlobSeer while running ./configure

		./configure --prefix= --with-postgresql= --with-blobseer= >& out &

Configuration
=============
See how to deploy Gfarm file system first.
	
	+ Configure BlobSeer (see BlobSeer)

	+ Configure Gfarm metadata server
		./config-gfarm --prefix $GFMD_DIR -S -m port -p back-end port (postgresSQL) (E.g. -m 5505 -p 6606)

	+ Configure Gfarm file system node
		./config-gfsd --prefix  -S -p 5506(port) $SPOOL_DIRECTORY

	+ Add these parameters to the gfarm configuration (gfsd.conf and gfarm.conf) file in order to work with BlobSeer
		+ In gfsd.conf
			BLOB_REPLICA_COUNT 1 (The number of replicas for each blob)
			BLOB_PAGE_SIZE 4194304 (Blob page size: 4 MB, should use a page size of 1 MB)
			BLOB_CONFIGURATION (path to BlobSeer configuration file)
		+ In gfarm.conf	
			BLOB_REPLICA_COUNT 1 (The number of replicas for each blob)
			BLOB_PAGE_SIZE 4194304 (Blob page size: 4 MB, should use a page size of 1 MB)
			BLOB_CONFIGURATION (path to BlobSeer configuration file)

Deployment
==========
	+Run BlobSeer
	+Run gfmd daemon	./gfmd start
	+Run gfsd daemon	./gfsd start

	+Mount Gfarm2fs if you want to use Gfarm/BlobSeer as a POSIX file system (see README of Gfarm2fs




	
